By Omololu Ogunmade President Muhammadu Buhari Wednesday condoled with former Governor of Ekiti State, Mr. Ayodele Fayose, over the demise of his elder sister, Mrs. Moji Ladeji.
A statement by the president’s spokesman, Mr. Femi Adesina, said Buhari prayed God to comfort Fayose on the sad loss of his sister.
Adesina also said the president condoled with the immediate family of the deceased as well as the Fayose and Ladeji’s friends, families, associates and relations, and urged them to take heart, moreso that death is the end of all mortals.
The statement read: “President Muhammadu Buhari prays God’s comfort for former Governor of Ekiti State, Ayo Fayose, on the sad loss of his immediate elder sister, Mrs Moji Ladeji.
“The President equally condoles with the nuclear family of the deceased, the larger Fayose and Ladeji families, friends, relations and associates, urging them to take heart, since death is the ultimate end of all mortals.
“President Buhari prays that the soul of the departed will rest in peace.”